article.headline: Yale 87, Army 79
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Greg Mangano scored 27 points and grabbed 15 rebounds to lead Yale over Army 87-79 on Saturday. The Bulldogs (2-3) scored 32 points in the paint, contributing to a 54.3 shooting percentage (25 of 46). Peter Braswell added 16, Austin Morgan 13 and Rhett Anderson and Reggie Willhite chipped in 12 each for Yale. The Bulldogs trailed 72-69 with 6:19 left before scoring nine straight over 3:31. Willhite gave Yale a 78-72 lead on two free throws with 2:30 to play. Yale trailed 26-17 midway through the first half before a 12-4 run gave the Bulldogs a 35-30 lead with 4:25 to go until halftime. Julian Simmons scored 28 points for the Black Knights (4-2), whose three-game winning streak ended. Simmons and Jason Pancoe, who finished with 16 points, made four 3s each as Army set a school record with 14 3-pointers (14 of 25).
